undoubtedly the decision of Société Nationale des Chemins de Fer Luxembourgeois (CFL), Northern Luxembourg’s industrial powerhouse since more than 70 years, to massively invest in industrial property development on the back of some strategic deals with big players in the industrial scene in Northern Luxembourg.

CFL already acts as a landlord to some of the biggest companies in the region,

among which Bomeli, Wecycle, Mulliez, Zoom or Still, but decided to move a step further in 2012, after winning the tender on the Caincourt site, a gorgeous greenfield site North of Pitch en Picardie, in Northern Luxembourg.

As a direct consequence of the Caincourt project, the XL Properties Group was established on May 2012 with a 2.5million € total equity stake – half coming from CFL – and was asked to design and draw up the masterplan, as well as build the industrial park.

The development of Caincourt is going very fast, and four building projects were already awarded out of the 3 million € first part of the additional capital, while the last one is shortly to be dispatched.

Construction is fully occupied, and budgets for 2013 are already designed.
